<span class="displaytext"><center><b><i>"i think the significant thing is what [senator (candidate last)'s] trying to work his way out of right now -- the statement that he made that he would negotiate with ahmadinejad and castro without preconditions. -- mayor (candidate full)</i></b></center> <p><b> fox news' "fox &amp; friends"</b><br/> <b>may 29, 2008</b></p><p><b>mayor (candidate full):</b> "i think the significant thing is what [senator (candidate last)'s] trying to work his way out of right now -- the statement that he made that he would negotiate with ahmadinejad and castro without preconditions. this is a statement that, in the words of (candidate full), was immature i think and naive and irresponsible. i think it was naive and irresponsible. this is the one thing (candidate full) and i agree on. it was naive, it was irresponsible, and it suggests that he doesn't have the right instincts to really handle tough diplomacy against really difficult people. that's a time honored rule of diplomacy, going back at least to my recollection of the summit meetings with khrushchev and kennedy and eisenhower. you have to have preconditions when you deal with these people." </p><p><b>fox news' gretchen carlson:</b> "(PARTY NAME) or (PARTY NAME)."</p><p><b>mayor (candidate last):</b> "i think it would be best for (candidate full) - not to take my advice - if he'd just admit this is an error and i don't have much experience and i made a mistake and i'm going to learn about it."</p><p><b>fox news' steve doocy:</b> "a do-over."</p><p><b><i><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhy-upkpk-0">watch</a> mayor (candidate last) on fox news' "fox &amp; friends"</i></b></p></span>



